{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9c3d09c5-cb79-453c-b2be-b28058b2153c","content":"For NativeAOT apps, the runtime doesn't bundle `createdump`, so you must explicitly point to it. Here are the pod spec changes:\n\n**Environment variables** on your container:\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  # Enable automatic crash dump on unhandled exceptions\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"\n  # Explicit path required for NativeAOT (no bundled createdump)\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n  # %d=PID, %p=process name, %t=timestamp\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%d.%p.%t\"\n```\n\n**Volume mount** so dumps survive container restarts:\n\n```yaml\nvolumeMounts:\n  - name: crash-dumps\n    mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n```\n\n**Volume** on the pod spec:\n\n```yaml\nvolumes:\n  - name: crash-dumps\n    emptyDir:\n      sizeLimit: 2Gi   # adjust based on expected dump size\n```\n\n**Security context** — `createdump` needs `SYS_PTRACE` to read process memory:\n\n```yaml\nsecurityContext:\n  capabilities:\n    add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` is critical for NativeAOT since the runtime won't find `createdump` on its own.\n- Use `emptyDir` for ephemeral collection; swap to a PersistentVolumeClaim if you need dumps to survive pod deletion.\n- Consider a sidecar or CronJob to upload dumps from `/tmp/dumps` to blob storage before they're lost.\n- Dump type `4` (Full) gives the most info but produces the largest files — use `2` (Heap) if space is tight.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"204a7aa8-a63e-4605-b38e-f66f0d0928b5","outputTokens":522,"requestId":"6007:2470A1:E2999C:105E1DF:69EACA77"},"id":"afdc99f6-90d0-41ae-9ce5-50be55c6c616","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:42:26.137Z","parentId":"d7a2ed68-ba3d-45ea-9ab3-255241ecfb07"}
